WEBVTT

1
00:00:48.695 --> 00:00:49.695
My goodness.

2
00:00:50.756 --> 00:00:52.026
(Congratulations on your return.)

3
00:00:57.335 --> 00:00:58.506
Thank you.

4
00:01:01.375 --> 00:01:02.506
Ha Ri.

5
00:01:04.175 --> 00:01:05.745
I loved your column.

6
00:01:05.875 --> 00:01:07.676
- Really? - Me too.

7
00:01:09.345 --> 00:01:10.375
I liked it, too.

8
00:01:10.815 --> 00:01:12.786
Thanks, you guys.

9
00:01:14.656 --> 00:01:17.856
Whether it was good or bad, you still need to come with me.

10
00:01:18.455 --> 00:01:21.926
But I just got here. I need to organize some stuff...

11
00:01:21.926 --> 00:01:22.955
Follow me.

12
00:01:30.036 --> 00:01:31.665
I'll convince the readers...

13
00:01:32.406 --> 00:01:34.265
like a true magazine journalist.

14
00:01:36.335 --> 00:01:37.735
"Convince"?

15
00:01:37.976 --> 00:01:40.175
I asked you to write an apology.

16
00:01:40.175 --> 00:01:42.875
Who told you to write a journal?

17
00:01:43.375 --> 00:01:44.615
Do you take this as a joke?

18
00:01:45.985 --> 00:01:47.645
How lightly do you take our readers?

19
00:01:48.955 --> 00:01:50.455
Aren't you scared of me?

20
00:02:24.216 --> 00:02:26.086
He didn't scold me as much as I thought he would.

21
00:02:26.586 --> 00:02:27.856
I'm so relieved.

22
00:02:29.425 --> 00:02:31.425
Drink up. It's on me.

23
00:02:31.966 --> 00:02:35.065
Are you buying because you know I'll get fired tomorrow?

24
00:02:36.395 --> 00:02:38.666
My gosh, I forgot my ID for the job search site.

25
00:02:39.865 --> 00:02:41.836
My resignation letter will act as your weapon.

26
00:02:43.505 --> 00:02:45.906
I understand why the company is so angry.

27
00:02:46.206 --> 00:02:48.815
But I will have to start over once I have a career break.

28
00:02:48.815 --> 00:02:51.516
And it's hard to get another job as editor-in-chief.

29
00:02:52.045 --> 00:02:54.986
Plus, I'm too old to study something new and start anew.

30
00:02:56.486 --> 00:02:58.855
So you're just going to quit?

31
00:03:01.295 --> 00:03:03.695
My baby had a febrile seizure.

32
00:03:04.095 --> 00:03:05.665
If it gets worse, it could cause epilepsy.

33
00:03:05.665 --> 00:03:07.125
So I need to be with him.

34
00:03:08.535 --> 00:03:09.936
It's nothing serious.

35
00:03:10.896 --> 00:03:13.906
But I can't even take care of my firstborn either.

36
00:03:14.466 --> 00:03:17.035
I forgot to pack his blanket, so for the past week,

37
00:03:17.035 --> 00:03:19.375
he had to take naps at the daycare center without one.

38
00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:22.345
I felt so sorry that I got angry at myself.

39
00:03:24.276 --> 00:03:25.586
So I'm going to quit.

40
00:03:28.355 --> 00:03:31.216
But this is too sudden.

41
00:03:31.216 --> 00:03:33.526
That way, they won't be able to fire you.

42
00:03:34.156 --> 00:03:35.426
You're the only person...

43
00:03:35.426 --> 00:03:37.825
who's been working here for 15 years.

44
00:03:38.095 --> 00:03:40.695
No one in the company has shown more loyalty or affection than you have.

45
00:03:41.396 --> 00:03:43.766
What's so wrong about not having a baby?

46
00:03:44.595 --> 00:03:46.406
I guess having a baby could help gain credibility,

47
00:03:46.406 --> 00:03:48.475
but I can't even take care of my own baby properly.

48
00:03:52.505 --> 00:03:54.605
- Ms. Shim. - I'm going to quit...

49
00:03:54.716 --> 00:03:57.075
after I make sure you become the editor-in-chief.

50
00:03:57.415 --> 00:03:59.146
And this is solely out of my personal interest.

51
00:03:59.986 --> 00:04:01.285
I may have been mean to you,

52
00:04:01.285 --> 00:04:03.686
but you were the only one who truly understood me.

53
00:04:04.785 --> 00:04:06.926
I want you to become the editor-in-chief.

54
00:04:11.896 --> 00:04:12.966
Drink up.

55
00:04:33.716 --> 00:04:35.785
The treatment didn't work last time.

56
00:04:36.656 --> 00:04:38.026
Would you still like to give it another try?

57
00:04:49.236 --> 00:04:51.165
What if you meet someone you love?

58
00:04:51.706 --> 00:04:54.435
So you've never once wanted to be a dad?

59
00:04:56.175 --> 00:04:57.506
No, never.

60
00:04:59.845 --> 00:05:02.216
Who knew you'd make my heart ache like this?

61
00:05:19.396 --> 00:05:20.896
Stop it.

62
00:05:20.896 --> 00:05:23.165
Jae Young, stop it already!

63
00:05:23.935 --> 00:05:25.305
- Hey! - Wait.

64
00:05:25.665 --> 00:05:27.865
Let go! Stop it!

65
00:05:40.115 --> 00:05:41.415
Mr. Han!

66
00:06:00.506 --> 00:06:01.506
What are you doing?

67
00:06:06.146 --> 00:06:09.376
You don't seem that happy to see me.

68
00:06:10.516 --> 00:06:13.446
It looks like you want to be alone. I'll just leave.

69
00:06:15.855 --> 00:06:17.016
Don't go.

70
00:06:20.225 --> 00:06:21.595
Let's chat.

71
00:06:30.435 --> 00:06:31.605
What did you do today?

72
00:06:35.136 --> 00:06:38.076
Life felt like a math problem, so I was trying to solve it.

73
00:06:39.876 --> 00:06:43.646
I want to get the right answer, but it's quite hard.

74
00:06:45.985 --> 00:06:47.345
That's deep.

75
00:06:47.485 --> 00:06:49.586
Did I ask you a philosophical question?

76
00:06:50.415 --> 00:06:53.785
"I slacked off after I finished my work."

77
00:06:54.185 --> 00:06:57.355
"Then I came for a walk in the park and suddenly thought of you."

78
00:06:57.925 --> 00:06:59.665
I was expecting something more like that.

79
00:07:01.396 --> 00:07:02.696
Wait. Why would you think of me?

80
00:07:07.605 --> 00:07:08.805
I know, right?

81
00:07:09.605 --> 00:07:13.206
Why would I suddenly think of you?

82
00:07:18.886 --> 00:07:20.545
You could've thought of me.

83
00:07:21.615 --> 00:07:25.185
We ran into each other often here, and we're neighbors.

84
00:07:25.425 --> 00:07:28.396
You might wonder what I'm doing and when I might...

85
00:07:29.095 --> 00:07:30.626
come out for a walk.

86
00:07:31.295 --> 00:07:33.365
You seemed a bit weird.

87
00:07:33.995 --> 00:07:37.766
Normally, people pretend to be fine even though they're hurt.

88
00:07:38.735 --> 00:07:40.466
They hide their scars...

89
00:07:41.165 --> 00:07:42.975
and try their best to look okay.

90
00:07:44.376 --> 00:07:46.975
But every time I'm with you,

91
00:07:47.776 --> 00:07:50.675
I suddenly feel embarrassed...

92
00:07:51.615 --> 00:07:53.316
for trying to act so tough.

93
00:07:57.855 --> 00:08:00.326
You were so shocked that you asked a guy to marry you...

94
00:08:01.055 --> 00:08:04.626
even though you didn't like him that much.

95
00:08:07.066 --> 00:08:08.435
But on top of that,

96
00:08:09.735 --> 00:08:11.805
you even confessed that to the world.

97
00:08:12.506 --> 00:08:14.466
You're so brave, Ms. Jang.

98
00:08:20.276 --> 00:08:22.045
I'm saying this because I'm drunk.

99
00:08:23.175 --> 00:08:24.576
Ms. Jang.

100
00:08:26.316 --> 00:08:27.646
Good job.

101
00:08:36.225 --> 00:08:37.555
I'll do this...

102
00:08:38.826 --> 00:08:40.266
instead of giving you a stamp.

103
00:09:02.785 --> 00:09:05.555
I feel so much better thanks to you.

104
00:09:07.026 --> 00:09:08.325
Thank you...

105
00:09:08.996 --> 00:09:10.195
for acknowledging me.

106
00:09:14.925 --> 00:09:16.065
Mom.

107
00:09:17.136 --> 00:09:18.335
I Sang.

108
00:09:19.406 --> 00:09:20.805
Go home safely.

109
00:09:22.736 --> 00:09:25.276
You should've called before you came.

110
00:09:25.575 --> 00:09:28.915
No, it's okay. I know you're busy.

111
00:09:29.715 --> 00:09:33.116
I left the fermented flounder in the security office.

112
00:09:33.516 --> 00:09:36.455
But who is she?

113
00:09:39.486 --> 00:09:40.726
Hello.

114
00:09:40.756 --> 00:09:42.496
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

115
00:09:42.496 --> 00:09:45.496
She's just a colleague. Let's go home.

116
00:09:47.065 --> 00:09:50.465
I'm not really interested in seeing your place.

117
00:09:50.465 --> 00:09:52.805
Let me go. Let go.

118
00:09:53.835 --> 00:09:56.035
What's your name?

119
00:09:56.035 --> 00:09:58.746
My name is Jang Ha Ri.

120
00:09:58.906 --> 00:10:00.346
"Ha Ri"?

121
00:10:02.045 --> 00:10:04.616
You're beautiful, and so is your name.

122
00:10:04.776 --> 00:10:06.016
Thank you.

123
00:10:07.616 --> 00:10:09.016
You should go.

124
00:10:09.986 --> 00:10:12.185
- Let me help you get home. - What?

125
00:10:12.825 --> 00:10:14.226
Just wait a second.

126
00:10:15.596 --> 00:10:18.366
You two must be coming back from somewhere.

127
00:10:20.795 --> 00:10:22.366
Anyway, don't worry.

128
00:10:22.795 --> 00:10:25.906
I never step foot inside his house,

129
00:10:26.305 --> 00:10:29.305
so come by to have fun whenever you like.

130
00:10:29.305 --> 00:10:31.006
Ma'am, we're not...

131
00:10:31.006 --> 00:10:33.175
You have the wrong idea about us.

132
00:10:33.175 --> 00:10:35.045
You should get going. Gosh, I'm sorry.

133
00:10:35.045 --> 00:10:36.376
- Mother... - Good job, I Sang.

134
00:10:36.376 --> 00:10:38.016
- Mom, please. - Good job!

135
00:10:38.215 --> 00:10:39.386
- Don't be like this. - Wait.

136
00:10:39.445 --> 00:10:40.915
- Hold on. - Mom, please.

137
00:10:41.285 --> 00:10:43.415
- Please head home. - I like him, ma'am.

138
00:10:44.285 --> 00:10:45.555
- What? - That's right.

139
00:10:49.656 --> 00:10:51.656
I like Mr. Han.

140
00:10:54.325 --> 00:10:55.965
My gosh.

141
00:10:58.465 --> 00:10:59.565
Do you really?

142
00:11:00.106 --> 00:11:02.136
So please don't worry.

143
00:11:02.535 --> 00:11:04.575
Right, my gosh.

144
00:11:05.406 --> 00:11:07.976
Thank you so much. Thank you.

145
00:11:10.215 --> 00:11:11.986
Here's my cab.

146
00:11:12.616 --> 00:11:14.815
- I'll see you around. - Good night, ma'am.

147
00:11:16.555 --> 00:11:19.555
I Sang, take care!

148
00:12:03.996 --> 00:12:05.665
- What? - Have you had dinner?

149
00:12:05.766 --> 00:12:07.535
Of course. Do you know what time it is?

150
00:12:07.665 --> 00:12:09.606
- Did you have tripe? - Why tripe?

151
00:12:09.606 --> 00:12:11.506
They never serve just one portion.

152
00:12:12.276 --> 00:12:13.506
I already had dinner.

153
00:12:13.506 --> 00:12:15.075
It's why I'm telling you to eat tripe.

154
00:12:15.075 --> 00:12:16.476
Wash up and go to bed.

155
00:12:16.575 --> 00:12:17.715
I quit eating tripe.

156
00:12:36.565 --> 00:12:38.266
Did I do something wrong?

157
00:12:46.506 --> 00:12:48.846
Why is everything so easy with you?

158
00:12:49.675 --> 00:12:52.386
Your mother seemed worried, so...

159
00:12:52.585 --> 00:12:54.215
How can you love someone depending on what you see?

160
00:12:55.656 --> 00:12:56.815
We're not kids anymore...

161
00:12:59.425 --> 00:13:01.026
We know better now...

162
00:13:01.226 --> 00:13:04.026
than to begin a relationship neither of us can handle.

163
00:13:07.126 --> 00:13:08.965
Why is everything so complicated?

164
00:13:13.266 --> 00:13:14.366
Because I know how it'll end.

165
00:13:17.976 --> 00:13:19.146
You...

166
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:22.376
want kids.

167
00:13:27.215 --> 00:13:29.415
I don't.

168
00:13:31.256 --> 00:13:33.555
You'll end up getting hurt...

169
00:13:34.156 --> 00:13:36.356
and I won't be responsible for that.

170
00:13:36.996 --> 00:13:38.096
Mr. Han,

171
00:13:41.695 --> 00:13:43.766
my feelings are for me to handle.

172
00:13:51.006 --> 00:13:53.705
I guess I got carried away and made a mistake.

173
00:13:55.516 --> 00:13:57.545
From now on, please watch your actions...

174
00:13:58.585 --> 00:14:00.146
so that I don't get the wrong idea.

175
00:14:26.175 --> 00:14:27.675
What a pathetic pity party.

176
00:14:29.616 --> 00:14:30.915
And you said you wouldn't eat.

177
00:14:30.915 --> 00:14:32.585
You should've suggested alcohol.

178
00:14:32.585 --> 00:14:33.846
But I'm not going to have any.

179
00:14:35.915 --> 00:14:38.726
How can you eat tripe without soju?

180
00:14:38.986 --> 00:14:40.085
I don't want to get drunk.

181
00:14:40.486 --> 00:14:42.455
Whoever it is...

182
00:14:42.455 --> 00:14:44.856
shouldn't make you pity yourself.

183
00:14:47.195 --> 00:14:48.366
What guy?

184
00:14:48.596 --> 00:14:49.736
Sure, whatever.

185
00:14:54.866 --> 00:14:56.535
I can't believe...

186
00:14:57.435 --> 00:14:58.805
I read so much into it.

187
00:15:01.606 --> 00:15:02.646
It?

188
00:15:02.646 --> 00:15:05.886
I solidified my life's goal with how it didn't need to involve men,

189
00:15:09.555 --> 00:15:11.715
but the incident made my mind go fuzzy.

190
00:15:16.695 --> 00:15:19.295
Are you perhaps talking about a kiss?

191
00:15:20.195 --> 00:15:22.165
I lost my judgment...

192
00:15:22.695 --> 00:15:23.965
because it hadn't happened in a while.

193
00:15:25.266 --> 00:15:26.366
Did you sleep with him?

194
00:15:27.465 --> 00:15:29.976
What nonsense are you spewing?

195
00:15:30.506 --> 00:15:33.045
- And lower your voice. - My gosh.

196
00:15:36.215 --> 00:15:37.746
As long as it didn't happen.

197
00:15:38.785 --> 00:15:39.945
Unbelievable.

198
00:15:40.246 --> 00:15:41.846
Your world can spin...

199
00:15:44.756 --> 00:15:46.356
at a single touch or gaze...

200
00:15:47.226 --> 00:15:48.455
even when you're almost 40.

201
00:15:50.596 --> 00:15:52.626
You're better off living alone.

202
00:16:01.636 --> 00:16:04.776
Why would you fall for a guy who doesn't make a move?

203
00:16:04.776 --> 00:16:06.006
Forget about him already.

204
00:16:10.646 --> 00:16:12.215
It would've been different if he were 20.

205
00:16:13.215 --> 00:16:17.116
He wouldn't be this hesitant if he were still 30.

206
00:16:20.785 --> 00:16:22.596
Just like I'm running out of time,

207
00:16:24.896 --> 00:16:27.026
he must have his reasons for pushing me away.

208
00:16:27.026 --> 00:16:28.935
Why are you trying to understand him?

209
00:16:28.935 --> 00:16:30.736
Who cares about what he's going through?

210
00:16:31.665 --> 00:16:32.906
You said you were out of time.

211
00:16:36.175 --> 00:16:39.776
I'm a doctor, so why didn't you tell me about your condition?

212
00:16:41.006 --> 00:16:43.876
I didn't know that pediatricians dealt with infertility too.

213
00:16:44.045 --> 00:16:45.785
We can all consult on medical matters.

214
00:16:48.016 --> 00:16:49.215
Unbelievable.

215
00:16:51.215 --> 00:16:52.585
So what is it that you want?

216
00:16:53.285 --> 00:16:55.325
You said you didn't have the time to date and get married...

217
00:16:55.496 --> 00:16:57.896
nor have you been happy because of a guy.

218
00:17:02.996 --> 00:17:04.266
Is it still romance you want though?

219
00:17:06.705 --> 00:17:09.636
It hurts to finally let go, you know.

220
00:17:14.445 --> 00:17:17.215
Anyway, I would've given anything to be 20 today.

221
00:17:20.116 --> 00:17:22.585
Then I would've clung onto him as if there's no tomorrow.

222
00:17:30.555 --> 00:17:36.896
(Episode 7: The Realistic Distance that Doesn't Cause a Heartbreak)

223
00:17:36.896 --> 00:17:38.566
(Episode 7: The Realistic Distance that Doesn't Cause a Heartbreak)

224
00:17:43.876 --> 00:17:46.505
The background can be out of focus.

225
00:17:47.975 --> 00:17:51.046
How can I do that when there's no background?

226
00:17:51.175 --> 00:17:52.415
Is this a joke?

227
00:17:52.685 --> 00:17:56.586
Can't you manage this vibe with that item we have?

228
00:17:56.715 --> 00:17:58.455
You could if you're a good photographer.

229
00:18:00.356 --> 00:18:02.356
At least bring me some decent props first.

230
00:18:02.356 --> 00:18:04.995
Also, it's not up to you to decide whether I'm good or not.

231
00:18:05.866 --> 00:18:07.965
You have a way of making things complicated, don't you?

232
00:18:07.965 --> 00:18:09.596
Why can't you just do as you're asked?

233
00:18:09.935 --> 00:18:11.096
Ms. Choi,

234
00:18:11.995 --> 00:18:13.965
Let's not cross the line, okay?

235
00:18:14.165 --> 00:18:17.336
Belittling someone else doesn't make you suddenly competent.

236
00:18:18.435 --> 00:18:19.505
Mr. Han.

237
00:18:23.616 --> 00:18:25.985
Please shoot the photo that Ms. Choi asked for.

238
00:18:36.156 --> 00:18:38.156
From planning the article, deciding on the photos,

239
00:18:38.156 --> 00:18:40.396
and choosing the props were all done by Ms. Choi.

240
00:18:40.925 --> 00:18:43.566
We'll evaluate the photos once we see them.

241
00:18:45.136 --> 00:18:48.465
A second photoshoot will only waste our time.

242
00:18:48.465 --> 00:18:50.036
Who are you to waste the time and effort...

243
00:18:50.136 --> 00:18:51.975
of the photographer and his crew?

244
00:18:51.975 --> 00:18:53.076
That also...

245
00:18:53.745 --> 00:18:56.745
is up to the journalist in charge.

246
00:19:02.586 --> 00:19:03.915
- Organize them like so. - Sure thing.

247
00:19:06.326 --> 00:19:07.386
What...

248
00:19:08.126 --> 00:19:09.225
Unbelievable.

249
00:19:14.165 --> 00:19:16.396
I took your side so that you can take responsibility.

250
00:19:17.735 --> 00:19:20.136
You know that this is your fault.

251
00:19:20.265 --> 00:19:22.406
I couldn't let him have the upper hand though...

252
00:19:22.406 --> 00:19:24.175
especially when he's an outside hire.

253
00:19:24.435 --> 00:19:26.775
Just because he was once a hotshot photographer...

254
00:19:26.775 --> 00:19:28.505
doesn't mean that he can undermine me.

255
00:19:30.076 --> 00:19:31.715
Do you consider me as your superior?

256
00:19:33.985 --> 00:19:35.286
The photographer and designer...

257
00:19:35.286 --> 00:19:36.985
are your partners, not your subordinates.

258
00:19:39.955 --> 00:19:41.455
I guess I should apologize.

259
00:19:42.755 --> 00:19:46.665
I didn't want to seem patronizing, so I didn't teach you properly.

260
00:19:47.366 --> 00:19:50.336
Who would be fond of being told what to do?

261
00:19:50.796 --> 00:19:53.235
I figured you'd watch and learn, but that was wrong of me.

262
00:19:55.205 --> 00:19:58.036
I don't intend to work here for very long.

263
00:19:58.136 --> 00:20:00.675
I know that you search for other jobs every day.

264
00:20:02.376 --> 00:20:03.846
Is that why you're slacking off?

265
00:20:04.915 --> 00:20:06.715
No way!

266
00:20:07.116 --> 00:20:08.515
I've been trying to do my best.

267
00:20:08.515 --> 00:20:10.255
Instead of trying to do well,

268
00:20:10.356 --> 00:20:11.915
actually do well.

269
00:20:12.386 --> 00:20:15.796
If you don't take pride in your work, work is just torture.

270
00:20:16.955 --> 00:20:18.656
I'm going to scold you from now on.

271
00:20:18.695 --> 00:20:21.366
I won't say it's good enough anymore.

272
00:20:21.826 --> 00:20:24.136
I'll hound you until you produce something better.

273
00:20:25.096 --> 00:20:28.005
So that wherever you go, you'll be respected for what you learned here.

274
00:20:32.306 --> 00:20:34.205
Put together a portfolio...

275
00:20:34.205 --> 00:20:36.616
that you can show proudly before you quit.

276
00:20:40.185 --> 00:20:41.515
Let's take a break.

277
00:20:50.225 --> 00:20:52.025
I chose the picture of the infertile couple.

278
00:20:56.066 --> 00:20:59.005
The kids must have learned from me because I was disrespectful to you.

279
00:21:00.366 --> 00:21:02.036
I'm sorry for making them mistreat you.

280
00:21:09.715 --> 00:21:10.775
Okay.

281
00:21:15.245 --> 00:21:16.415
I hope...

282
00:21:17.215 --> 00:21:18.586
you won't...

283
00:21:19.485 --> 00:21:21.725
be hurt because of...

284
00:21:22.826 --> 00:21:23.896
me.

285
00:21:27.896 --> 00:21:29.995
I guess I got carried away and made a mistake.

286
00:21:31.235 --> 00:21:33.366
From now on, please watch your actions...

287
00:21:34.265 --> 00:21:35.935
so that I don't get the wrong idea.

288
00:21:59.126 --> 00:22:00.396
I...

289
00:22:02.195 --> 00:22:04.596
broke up with my long-term girlfriend...

290
00:22:05.695 --> 00:22:07.066
after we were engaged.

291
00:22:08.465 --> 00:22:11.636
I gave up on the idea of marriage since then,

292
00:22:13.275 --> 00:22:15.175
and there are no kids in my future.

293
00:22:16.876 --> 00:22:18.675
I didn't want to like anyone again,

294
00:22:20.116 --> 00:22:21.646
but I got swept away.

295
00:22:22.786 --> 00:22:24.786
My motives were unclear.

296
00:22:25.786 --> 00:22:27.556
It's natural that you were misled.

297
00:22:29.596 --> 00:22:31.556
So I was mistaken.

298
00:22:32.096 --> 00:22:34.066
I thought hard about it,

299
00:22:35.866 --> 00:22:38.235
but I still like being alone.

300
00:22:39.636 --> 00:22:42.836
I had decided to live alone many years ago...

301
00:22:43.536 --> 00:22:45.735
and set my path in life accordingly.

302
00:22:54.086 --> 00:22:55.586
I'm sorry...

303
00:22:58.616 --> 00:22:59.656
for confusing you.

304
00:23:03.126 --> 00:23:04.455
I accept your apology.

305
00:23:05.965 --> 00:23:08.326
You didn't want to like anyone, right? Me too.

306
00:23:08.665 --> 00:23:11.465
It was brief, but it was too complicated and uncomfortable.

307
00:23:15.235 --> 00:23:17.205
- Let's not be awkward. - Okay.

308
00:23:17.705 --> 00:23:18.836
Let's not.

309
00:24:44.126 --> 00:24:45.296
It's so pretty.

310
00:25:12.116 --> 00:25:13.386
(Children's toothpaste Expiration Date Nov. 1, 2020)

311
00:25:13.386 --> 00:25:14.455
Are they all like that?

312
00:25:14.925 --> 00:25:16.896
What's wrong with them?

313
00:25:16.896 --> 00:25:18.626
Have you never received a barter before?

314
00:25:18.796 --> 00:25:20.725
These expire in six months.

315
00:25:21.025 --> 00:25:23.495
They dumped leftover inventory on us. What will you do about it?

316
00:25:23.796 --> 00:25:27.366
He's new at this. Cut him some slack.

317
00:25:27.366 --> 00:25:28.935
I was talking to you.

318
00:25:30.735 --> 00:25:31.806
Okay.

319
00:25:32.606 --> 00:25:33.745
Choi Hyo Joo.

320
00:25:33.806 --> 00:25:36.816
Didn't you tell Advertising to check expiration dates?

321
00:25:37.316 --> 00:25:39.546
Well. So, I...

322
00:25:40.515 --> 00:25:42.515
meant to tell him...

323
00:25:50.725 --> 00:25:52.556
I heard but forgot.

324
00:25:53.096 --> 00:25:54.265
I'm sorry.

325
00:25:58.566 --> 00:26:01.066
We can't distribute these as gifts to the readers.

326
00:26:01.536 --> 00:26:02.906
Get a new batch.

327
00:26:03.775 --> 00:26:05.675
How can we send these back?

328
00:26:05.675 --> 00:26:07.675
It was so hard to get...

329
00:26:11.415 --> 00:26:12.945
Just say it with words.

330
00:26:13.386 --> 00:26:15.286
Don't say it with your eyes.

331
00:26:15.286 --> 00:26:18.156
Take care of it and get a new batch.

332
00:26:19.326 --> 00:26:20.356
Okay.

333
00:26:25.096 --> 00:26:26.165
Got that?

334
00:26:26.396 --> 00:26:27.495
Yes, sir.

335
00:26:32.396 --> 00:26:33.435
Have a nice day.

336
00:26:35.866 --> 00:26:37.205
Yes, sir.

337
00:26:38.705 --> 00:26:39.775
Have a nice day.

338
00:26:54.425 --> 00:26:56.156
I meant to tell you,

339
00:26:56.596 --> 00:26:59.765
but I forgot because I was stunned by the counterfeit slippers.

340
00:27:01.626 --> 00:27:02.866
I see.

341
00:27:04.296 --> 00:27:07.665
Anyway, were you helping me?

342
00:27:11.876 --> 00:27:13.646
I didn't want you to get scolded.

343
00:27:15.106 --> 00:27:17.515
You were scolded already earlier. I thought you'd get angry...

344
00:27:17.515 --> 00:27:19.046
if you got scolded again.

345
00:27:19.846 --> 00:27:22.586
Why do you keep getting scolded, anyway?

346
00:27:22.786 --> 00:27:24.656
I get scolded because I'm new.

347
00:27:25.015 --> 00:27:26.656
I did not get scolded!

348
00:27:28.725 --> 00:27:30.195
I guess you're just an angry person.

349
00:27:32.896 --> 00:27:34.366
But you know,

350
00:27:34.725 --> 00:27:37.566
I tried to only say hello since that's what you said to do,

351
00:27:37.836 --> 00:27:41.306
but you keep talking to me.

352
00:27:43.306 --> 00:27:47.106
Are you arguing with me because I started a conversation?

353
00:27:47.546 --> 00:27:50.116
No, no. I prefer talking to you...

354
00:27:50.116 --> 00:27:52.116
over just saying hi.

355
00:27:54.015 --> 00:27:56.286
Shall we talk for a while next time too?

356
00:27:58.116 --> 00:28:00.786
I'll go now. Wish me luck.

357
00:28:05.995 --> 00:28:09.096
He just told me he likes me, didn't he?

358
00:28:09.695 --> 00:28:11.636
Talk about lame.

359
00:28:21.705 --> 00:28:24.475
What's with that smile? It's very annoying.

360
00:28:25.116 --> 00:28:26.286
What do you want?

361
00:28:27.215 --> 00:28:28.445
I just want to eat with you.

362
00:28:28.445 --> 00:28:30.586
Why would you come all the way here to buy me lunch?

363
00:28:30.685 --> 00:28:32.515
I don't want to eat alone, that's why.

364
00:28:32.826 --> 00:28:33.985
Let's go.

365
00:28:34.025 --> 00:28:37.356
You look like someone hitting on a girl.

366
00:28:37.556 --> 00:28:38.656
Just follow me!

367
00:28:44.866 --> 00:28:45.935
Here.

368
00:28:48.505 --> 00:28:51.606
I have no money. I have no time. I can't do anything.

369
00:28:52.376 --> 00:28:54.705
I just wanted to eat with you. That's why I came.

370
00:28:55.445 --> 00:28:57.475
Stop glaring at me. Let's enjoy our food.

371
00:28:58.915 --> 00:29:02.215
I thought about this, considering our 39-year-long friendship.

372
00:29:02.515 --> 00:29:05.386
You're terminally ill. You could die any day.

373
00:29:05.386 --> 00:29:08.485
Then there's no reason why I can't help you out.

374
00:29:10.755 --> 00:29:11.955
I'll marry you.

375
00:29:17.695 --> 00:29:20.435
Think about it for 5... No, 1 minute.

376
00:29:20.705 --> 00:29:22.636
Sure. It tastes good.

377
00:29:22.765 --> 00:29:24.435
Can you at least pretend to think about it?

378
00:29:30.116 --> 00:29:31.475
Honey, is dinner almost ready?

379
00:29:32.515 --> 00:29:34.046
Did you wash my socks?

380
00:29:34.245 --> 00:29:36.886
- Socks? - And I need my shirt ironed...

381
00:29:36.886 --> 00:29:39.185
nice and stiff for tomorrow.

382
00:29:39.415 --> 00:29:41.455
I'm going to soak in the tub after dinner,

383
00:29:41.685 --> 00:29:44.925
so draw a bath for me. I want the water at 39.5 degrees.

384
00:29:44.925 --> 00:29:46.156
I'm a bit sensitive.

385
00:29:47.126 --> 00:29:48.995
You're killing my appetite.

386
00:29:48.995 --> 00:29:51.195
Just hire a housekeeper.

387
00:29:51.265 --> 00:29:53.606
Why do you hate the idea that much?

388
00:29:53.665 --> 00:29:55.665
- Is it that bad? - Obviously, it isn't good.

389
00:29:55.836 --> 00:29:59.205
I appreciate the concern, but why are you risking our friendship?

390
00:29:59.275 --> 00:30:00.606
What's gotten into you lately?

391
00:30:00.846 --> 00:30:02.175
Am I that pitiful?

392
00:30:03.616 --> 00:30:05.915
Lately, I've been...

393
00:30:13.886 --> 00:30:15.086
I'm just lonely.

394
00:30:16.255 --> 00:30:17.396
Do you have andropause?

395
00:30:17.396 --> 00:30:19.995
Do you feel lonely, dejected, and suddenly find yourself in tears?

396
00:30:19.995 --> 00:30:21.665
No, it's more like puberty.

397
00:30:21.965 --> 00:30:24.495
My feelings are all over the place these days.

398
00:30:28.366 --> 00:30:29.836
So you should...

399
00:30:30.435 --> 00:30:32.945
look at me once in a while and make sure I stay on track.

400
00:30:40.445 --> 00:30:42.485
I am looking at you. Eat up.

401
00:30:45.185 --> 00:30:47.286
Make sure you chew. You don't want to get sick.

402
00:30:53.096 --> 00:30:54.296
You can wait here.

403
00:30:55.866 --> 00:30:58.235
I don't know when Mr. Park will come.

404
00:31:00.136 --> 00:31:01.836
I'm sure he'll come before he gets fired.

405
00:31:02.566 --> 00:31:03.636
Right.

406
00:31:13.346 --> 00:31:14.415
(Resignation Letter: Shim Jung Hwa, The Baby Editing Department)

407
00:31:14.415 --> 00:31:17.255
(I can no longer work here because I need to focus on childcare.)

408
00:31:33.066 --> 00:31:35.505
I never told you to quit.

409
00:31:35.965 --> 00:31:38.235
I only suggested you take a break.

410
00:31:38.806 --> 00:31:41.076
It was pretty much the same thing as telling me to quit.

411
00:31:41.646 --> 00:31:44.646
And it's time that I quit anyway.

412
00:31:44.745 --> 00:31:46.886
I need to leave in order for the others to get promoted.

413
00:31:50.856 --> 00:31:53.286
I can't ask you to stay because your baby is sick.

414
00:31:54.156 --> 00:31:57.925
Then can you at least work until we hire someone new?

415
00:31:58.025 --> 00:32:01.265
No, I'm going to hand over all my work to Ms. Jang...

416
00:32:01.265 --> 00:32:02.525
and quit right away.

417
00:32:06.165 --> 00:32:08.806
Just because you quit...

418
00:32:09.265 --> 00:32:12.005
doesn't mean Ms. Jang will become the editor-in-chief.

419
00:32:12.336 --> 00:32:13.705
She'll just be the acting editor-in-chief.

420
00:32:23.056 --> 00:32:24.455
I also care...

421
00:32:25.656 --> 00:32:27.656
about Ms. Jang.

422
00:32:27.925 --> 00:32:31.296
But the chairman is very angry with her,

423
00:32:31.296 --> 00:32:32.826
so she won't be able to take your place.

424
00:32:33.925 --> 00:32:36.896
So just keep working here until we find...

425
00:32:36.896 --> 00:32:38.536
someone to replace you.

426
00:32:39.435 --> 00:32:40.505
Okay.

427
00:32:43.836 --> 00:32:45.275
Have a good day.

428
00:32:48.445 --> 00:32:49.606
Hey, Seung Tae.

429
00:32:52.616 --> 00:32:54.786
Either be a loyal dog to the chairman...

430
00:32:55.415 --> 00:32:58.316
or be a good boss who takes good care of his subordinates.

431
00:32:59.955 --> 00:33:01.626
If you want to do both, then be good at it.

432
00:33:03.356 --> 00:33:04.796
Have a good day.

433
00:33:23.215 --> 00:33:25.175
Hey, you're here.

434
00:33:25.515 --> 00:33:26.745
Why didn't you go home?

435
00:33:28.046 --> 00:33:30.715
I spent the entire day at Cheonwang.

436
00:33:31.015 --> 00:33:32.786
But I didn't get to meet Mr. Park.

437
00:33:33.126 --> 00:33:35.126
I didn't do much today, so I thought I'd get some work done.

438
00:33:37.356 --> 00:33:39.326
You just waited there all day?

439
00:33:40.096 --> 00:33:41.396
Did Mr. Kim tell you to do that?

440
00:33:41.765 --> 00:33:43.366
It's my job, so I should be the one to take care of it.

441
00:33:45.465 --> 00:33:46.665
Ms. Jang.

442
00:33:48.136 --> 00:33:49.636
I learned a lot from your column.

443
00:33:50.136 --> 00:33:52.136
There was nothing to learn from it.

444
00:33:52.536 --> 00:33:55.475
I learned that I should make sure to keep my private life private.

445
00:33:57.015 --> 00:33:59.116
And I realized that I need to act more bravely.

446
00:34:02.846 --> 00:34:05.415
I'm too young to judge you.

447
00:34:05.755 --> 00:34:08.786
But I do think you're incredible.

448
00:34:09.856 --> 00:34:11.025
In what way?

449
00:34:12.126 --> 00:34:15.495
To be honest, I don't even know what I want.

450
00:34:16.126 --> 00:34:17.435
So I'm still very lost.

451
00:34:18.036 --> 00:34:21.366
But on the other hand, you know exactly...

452
00:34:21.366 --> 00:34:24.175
what you want, and that's how you live your life.

453
00:34:24.606 --> 00:34:27.705
To some people, it might seem unusual.

454
00:34:27.705 --> 00:34:30.415
And some people might be scared to take action like you.

455
00:34:32.215 --> 00:34:33.316
So I think you're amazing.

456
00:34:36.015 --> 00:34:39.386
Eu Ddeum, you understand me?

457
00:34:40.455 --> 00:34:42.855
Yes, what you want isn't illegal.

458
00:34:48.125 --> 00:34:49.996
- Goodbye. - See you.

459
00:34:49.996 --> 00:34:51.065
Bye.

460
00:34:58.036 --> 00:34:59.906
(Advertising Department, Choi Kang Eu Ddeum)

461
00:35:05.516 --> 00:35:06.746
It's due tomorrow.

462
00:35:07.315 --> 00:35:09.485
- Ms. Choi, look. - What?

463
00:35:09.485 --> 00:35:10.786
Don't I look exactly like Chow Yun-fat?

464
00:35:11.085 --> 00:35:13.016
What? Whom?

465
00:35:13.755 --> 00:35:14.855
She must not know him.

466
00:35:16.186 --> 00:35:18.755
By the way, is Eu Ddeum not here yet?

467
00:35:18.925 --> 00:35:20.496
He went straight to Cheonwang.

468
00:35:20.795 --> 00:35:23.835
Mr. Park, the team leader, is really petty.

469
00:35:23.835 --> 00:35:24.835
If he's at a disadvantage,

470
00:35:24.835 --> 00:35:27.235
he never answers our calls or agrees to meet us.

471
00:35:28.005 --> 00:35:30.036
You sent Eu Ddeum to a place like that?

472
00:35:30.735 --> 00:35:32.636
Why? Was I not supposed to send him there?

473
00:35:33.445 --> 00:35:36.916
He won't be able to do anything. He'll just get kicked out.

474
00:35:38.675 --> 00:35:40.246
Chow Yun-fat, my foot.

475
00:35:41.645 --> 00:35:42.786
What's wrong with her?

476
00:35:47.686 --> 00:35:50.895
- Hey, Ms. Choi. - Are you going to stay there?

477
00:35:51.826 --> 00:35:53.395
I should wait. It's my job.

478
00:35:53.395 --> 00:35:55.326
Don't bother. Just come back.

479
00:35:56.366 --> 00:35:57.465
What's the matter?

480
00:35:58.465 --> 00:36:01.366
I need you to help me with some stuff.

481
00:36:01.565 --> 00:36:03.235
I'm piled with stuff to do.

482
00:36:03.235 --> 00:36:05.906
Anyway, there's tons of work, so just get over here.

483
00:36:12.576 --> 00:36:14.516
Who was that? Was it Eu Ddeum?

484
00:36:15.786 --> 00:36:18.585
Yes, he's still at Cheonwang.

485
00:36:18.855 --> 00:36:20.956
He's so naive. They're never going to meet him,

486
00:36:21.255 --> 00:36:22.755
but he's just waiting there.

487
00:36:24.425 --> 00:36:26.895
Why would he send Eu Ddeum to a place like that?

488
00:36:27.766 --> 00:36:30.496
Don't you think this is a bit too much?

489
00:36:32.036 --> 00:36:35.366
Yeon Ho, do we have the proposal for Cheonwang's company magazine?

490
00:36:36.005 --> 00:36:37.136
Just a second.

491
00:36:42.505 --> 00:36:43.545
Do you have a meeting here?

492
00:36:43.545 --> 00:36:44.875
We're scheduled to have a meeting here at 11am.

493
00:36:45.875 --> 00:36:47.246
No, you can use this place.

494
00:36:48.016 --> 00:36:49.085
I'll go.

495
00:36:52.255 --> 00:36:53.485
Sorry. Bye.

496
00:37:04.465 --> 00:37:06.636
Ms. Park sent us the proposal.

497
00:37:06.806 --> 00:37:08.565
There weren't any problems with it.

498
00:37:11.206 --> 00:37:12.275
Where...

499
00:37:20.416 --> 00:37:21.516
Eu Ddeum.

500
00:37:23.215 --> 00:37:27.386
What? Ms. Jang, what are you doing here?

501
00:37:29.625 --> 00:37:32.326
The problem is right there.

502
00:37:37.065 --> 00:37:39.065
Do you expect your subcontractors to do everything you ask...

503
00:37:39.065 --> 00:37:40.605
and get punished like this?

504
00:37:41.436 --> 00:37:43.706
No, he wasn't there getting punished.

505
00:37:43.706 --> 00:37:46.706
When you're a new recruit, you get intimidated by your boss,

506
00:37:46.706 --> 00:37:50.175
you chew over your mistakes, and you punish yourself...

507
00:37:50.445 --> 00:37:52.645
by wondering if you should just write a resignation letter.

508
00:37:53.076 --> 00:37:54.715
He's already having a hard time as it is.

509
00:37:54.985 --> 00:37:58.715
So the least you can do is to treat him with respect.

510
00:38:01.585 --> 00:38:02.656
I'm sorry.

511
00:38:03.085 --> 00:38:05.355
I should've been more considerate, but I was just so busy.

512
00:38:10.666 --> 00:38:11.735
Okay.

513
00:38:12.036 --> 00:38:15.036
Sir, you're giving us work because you trust us.

514
00:38:15.206 --> 00:38:18.436
Our company believes that we have a good relationship with Cheonwang.

515
00:38:18.906 --> 00:38:21.645
And I hope to continue that relationship with you guys.

516
00:38:24.516 --> 00:38:27.386
- I'll call Mr. Park for you. - Thank you.

517
00:38:29.715 --> 00:38:31.315
Sir, just a second.

518
00:38:34.255 --> 00:38:37.855
Hello, I'm Jang Ha Ri from The Baby.

519
00:38:38.496 --> 00:38:40.326
I'm here regarding the toothpaste.

520
00:38:40.666 --> 00:38:44.235
It seems like you're busy, so I'll just talk to the director.

521
00:38:44.295 --> 00:38:46.906
If not, I'll just talk to the chairman.

522
00:39:03.755 --> 00:39:05.315
Look at how successful you've become.

523
00:39:06.186 --> 00:39:07.386
Mr. Han!

524
00:39:08.485 --> 00:39:09.585
Mr. Han?

525
00:39:09.585 --> 00:39:11.795
- It's so nice to meet you. - I know.

526
00:39:11.956 --> 00:39:13.666
Does she have to say hello to him like that?

527
00:39:13.666 --> 00:39:15.925
- You made a lot of money. - Yes, a bit.

528
00:39:16.895 --> 00:39:18.235
- Have you been well? - Of course.

529
00:39:18.235 --> 00:39:19.996
I can't believe he's fine enough to smile.

530
00:39:20.366 --> 00:39:23.436
He couldn't even kiss me, but he seems fine with hugging her.

