I'm sorry.

799
00:57:31.718 --> 00:57:33.419
If it's better to quit cold turkey,

800
00:57:34.689 --> 00:57:35.828
I'll try that.

801
00:57:39.328 --> 00:57:41.328
Ha Ri, did you find them all?

802
00:57:41.799 --> 00:57:43.268
Yes, almost.

803
00:57:45.198 --> 00:57:48.908
Who knew Ms. Shim would quit because of her baby?

804
00:57:49.538 --> 00:57:52.209
I don't think I could handle it if my baby were sick.

805
00:57:52.379 --> 00:57:54.678
No matter how you look at it, I was smart not to have kids.

806
00:57:56.549 --> 00:57:58.018
- Yeon Ho? - Yes?

807
00:57:58.348 --> 00:58:01.819
Do you think you'll never change your mind?

808
00:58:02.288 --> 00:58:05.189
We're living happy, fun lives, just the two of us.

809
00:58:05.388 --> 00:58:07.988
I don't want to sacrifice my life for a baby.

810
00:58:08.229 --> 00:58:10.259
But realistically speaking, money is the biggest problem.

811
00:58:11.129 --> 00:58:13.959
We need to pay for their tuition until they graduate college,

812
00:58:14.029 --> 00:58:15.698
pay for their wedding,

813
00:58:15.768 --> 00:58:19.098
and we'll grow old while trying to help them buy a house.

814
00:58:19.138 --> 00:58:21.709
Then we'll never be able to enjoy our lives.

815
00:58:22.808 --> 00:58:24.468
We both don't want children,

816
00:58:24.468 --> 00:58:27.379
so telling us to have a baby is the same thing as verbal violence.

817
00:58:29.509 --> 00:58:32.218
I guess you're right. You do have a point.

818
00:58:34.749 --> 00:58:36.089
How is your project going?

819
00:58:36.149 --> 00:58:38.058
Why don't you just marry that guy?

820
00:58:38.058 --> 00:58:40.018
That's nonsense.

821
00:58:43.428 --> 00:58:45.698
Now that he's offering to give it to me, it's kind of scary.

822
00:58:45.859 --> 00:58:47.129
I also feel a bit sorry.

823
00:58:48.198 --> 00:58:49.899
I don't know if it's because he's young,

824
00:58:51.029 --> 00:58:53.268
but he's so slow-witted. He's just always so happy.

825
00:58:53.999 --> 00:58:56.009
What? Are you talking about Eu Ddeum?

826
00:58:58.779 --> 00:59:02.448
You're so quick-witted. Make sure you keep it a secret.

827
00:59:03.479 --> 00:59:06.419
I thought it was Mr. Han.

828
00:59:06.919 --> 00:59:08.288
No, it's not him.

829
00:59:08.988 --> 00:59:10.618
Eu Ddeum is too young.

830
00:59:10.788 --> 00:59:12.959
I'm just too old.

831
00:59:13.319 --> 00:59:16.058
I never knew I'd be so sad about my age.

832
00:59:17.428 --> 00:59:20.259
I don't know why I feel this way anymore.

833
00:59:21.229 --> 00:59:23.428
I don't know what to say to Eu Ddeum either.

834
00:59:30.439 --> 00:59:31.578
What?

835
00:59:33.339 --> 00:59:35.348
What am I going to do?

836
00:59:40.279 --> 00:59:41.419
Okay.

837
00:59:44.488 --> 00:59:45.518
Cheers.

838
00:59:45.618 --> 00:59:47.259
I get what you mean.

839
00:59:48.359 --> 00:59:50.928
My gosh, this tastes great.

840
00:59:50.928 --> 00:59:52.629
It's been ages since we drank.

841
00:59:53.759 --> 00:59:54.968
- Cheers. - It's delicious.

842
00:59:56.169 --> 00:59:58.138
We haven't gathered in ages.

843
00:59:59.799 --> 01:00:01.868
Attention, everyone.

844
01:00:02.038 --> 01:00:04.569
Do you all know why we're here?

845
01:00:04.678 --> 01:00:06.538
- To throw a farewell party... - For Ms. Shim!

846
01:00:09.049 --> 01:00:10.948
Yes, you guys are so thrilled.

847
01:00:10.948 --> 01:00:14.018
You must feel really upset to see how thrilled they are.

848
01:00:14.419 --> 01:00:16.288
Let's hear her say her last words before she leaves.

849
01:00:16.988 --> 01:00:18.158
Do you want me to take back my resignation letter?

850
01:00:18.359 --> 01:00:20.058
We'll skip that. Okay then.

851
01:00:20.319 --> 01:00:22.589
We prepared a huge gift for you...

852
01:00:22.589 --> 01:00:25.129
to wish you a happy farewell.

853
01:00:25.229 --> 01:00:27.759
Okay, bring the gift.

854
01:00:30.029 --> 01:00:31.268
Go and get it.

855
01:00:31.569 --> 01:00:33.368
- Go on. - Come on, Ms. Shim.

856
01:00:33.439 --> 01:00:34.768
- Gosh, do I have to? - Go on.

857
01:00:35.768 --> 01:00:36.768
Come on.

858
01:00:57.259 --> 01:01:00.629
We gathered all the articles you wrote.

859
01:01:01.058 --> 01:01:03.399
You can use it as a portfolio for your next job interview.

860
01:01:04.839 --> 01:01:06.169
Thank you.

861
01:01:07.169 --> 01:01:09.538
What's with the mood?

862
01:01:09.538 --> 01:01:10.868
Sing.

863
01:01:11.339 --> 01:01:13.979
- Sing. - Sing.

864
01:01:15.049 --> 01:01:17.408
That's enough.

865
01:01:19.678 --> 01:01:21.649
We don't get to do this that often.

866
01:01:22.118 --> 01:01:23.348
My goodness.

867
01:01:23.348 --> 01:01:24.488
Drink up.

868
01:01:25.359 --> 01:01:27.218
Let's ask I Sang.

869
01:01:27.218 --> 01:01:28.459
Okay, great.

870
01:01:28.459 --> 01:01:30.529
- Let's drink. - Here.

871
01:01:30.529 --> 01:01:32.058
Let's start today.

872
01:01:32.129 --> 01:01:33.558
Gosh, stop it.

873
01:01:33.859 --> 01:01:35.098
You need to pull it out.

874
01:01:36.529 --> 01:01:37.768
I won't go.

875
01:01:38.098 --> 01:01:39.968
Whoever goes home first will be considered a traitor.

876
01:01:39.968 --> 01:01:41.268
Let's go to a karaoke room.

877
01:01:41.268 --> 01:01:43.709
No, I can't sing.

878
01:01:43.939 --> 01:01:45.939
My gosh, that's enough.

879
01:01:46.709 --> 01:01:47.839
Stop.

880
01:01:49.049 --> 01:01:50.549
Let's go home after this.

881
01:01:51.109 --> 01:01:53.218
Gosh, no way.

882
01:01:54.678 --> 01:01:56.189
This is enough.

883
01:01:56.189 --> 01:01:57.788
Let's just call it a day.

884
01:01:57.788 --> 01:01:59.319
Don't even think of going home.

885
01:02:06.658 --> 01:02:08.529
I knew you'd be here.

886
01:02:08.529 --> 01:02:10.968
Why are you packing your stuff in the middle of a farewell party?

887
01:02:12.198 --> 01:02:13.598
Because I don't want to come to work tomorrow.

888
01:02:13.598 --> 01:02:16.138
You're not going to say goodbye just because you're embarrassed?

889
01:02:17.069 --> 01:02:20.038
You should come tomorrow. Let's eat lunch together.

890
01:02:20.738 --> 01:02:22.408
And let us see you off.

891
01:02:22.408 --> 01:02:23.879
Gosh, I can't be bothered.

892
01:02:24.408 --> 01:02:26.718
Just go take care of the others. They're all drunk.

893
01:02:26.848 --> 01:02:29.788
No, I'm going to take care of you.

894
01:02:32.419 --> 01:02:33.459
You're too nice.

895
01:02:33.459 --> 01:02:35.788
Don't be kind to everyone once you become the editor-in-chief.

896
01:02:35.788 --> 01:02:37.328
You need to be harsh whenever it's necessary.

897
01:02:37.328 --> 01:02:38.859
I wonder if they'll ever give me that position.

898
01:02:39.299 --> 01:02:42.468
If they don't, let me know. I'll come back with my baby.

899
01:02:43.098 --> 01:02:44.598
It feels like you really mean it.

900
01:02:47.868 --> 01:02:49.238
- Aren't you coming? - Okay.

901
01:02:53.808 --> 01:02:55.078
Wait for me.

902
01:02:55.249 --> 01:02:56.509
Hurry up.

903
01:03:02.819 --> 01:03:04.419
Are you really going to leave?

904
01:03:04.749 --> 01:03:08.058
You should at least say goodbye. It's your last time.

905
01:03:08.259 --> 01:03:10.388
And do what? Hug everyone and cry?

906
01:03:11.158 --> 01:03:13.198
It'll be embarrassing when we meet again.

907
01:03:13.529 --> 01:03:17.129
You're right. It'll be really embarrassing.

908
01:03:20.598 --> 01:03:23.468
- My gosh, Ms. Shim. - Hey.

909
01:03:23.808 --> 01:03:25.279
I might hit you.

910
01:03:33.118 --> 01:03:34.779
Thank you for everything.

911
01:03:38.689 --> 01:03:41.558
Thank you so much.

912
01:03:46.029 --> 01:03:47.259
Me too.

913
01:03:48.629 --> 01:03:49.899
Thank you for everything.

914
01:03:52.768 --> 01:03:53.868
Did you call for a chauffeur service?

915
01:03:54.768 --> 01:03:55.839
- Yes. - My gosh.

916
01:03:56.939 --> 01:03:58.538
You're so harsh.

917
01:04:42.319 --> 01:04:44.618
My gosh, let's go.

918
01:04:45.158 --> 01:04:46.759
My goodness.

919
01:04:46.759 --> 01:04:49.058
- Let's go! - Come on!

920
01:04:49.259 --> 01:04:51.189
Let's drink some more!

921
01:04:51.629 --> 01:04:53.729
Come on! Let's go for a drink!

922
01:04:54.729 --> 01:04:55.729
Let's drink more!

923
01:04:56.629 --> 01:04:58.229
- Come on. - Let's go for a second round.

924
01:04:58.229 --> 01:04:59.499
Let's drink some more.

925
01:04:59.499 --> 01:05:00.499
Go home.

926
01:05:01.808 --> 01:05:03.308
Just go home.

927
01:05:03.468 --> 01:05:05.509
- Stop it. - Just get in the car.

928
01:05:05.509 --> 01:05:07.279
- My gosh. - You guys should go.

929
01:05:07.279 --> 01:05:09.348
I'll take care of them.

930
01:05:09.678 --> 01:05:11.209
- You should go. - Okay, bye!

931
01:05:11.209 --> 01:05:12.779
- Bye! - Bye!

932
01:05:13.848 --> 01:05:15.919
Let's go for another round!

933
01:05:16.319 --> 01:05:18.288
- Come on! - I need to get some rest.

934
01:05:18.819 --> 01:05:20.988
Are we going for a second round?

935
01:05:20.988 --> 01:05:22.488
Just get in the car.

936
01:05:23.388 --> 01:05:24.589
My gosh.

937
01:05:24.729 --> 01:05:26.799
- That's not the door. - My goodness.

938
01:05:26.799 --> 01:05:28.828
- Let's go. - Wait here.

939
01:05:28.828 --> 01:05:30.669
Sir, get in.

940
01:05:30.669 --> 01:05:32.399
- Get in the car. - Okay.

941
01:05:32.669 --> 01:05:34.638
Eu Ddeum, wake up.

942
01:05:34.638 --> 01:05:35.868
Get up.

943
01:05:35.868 --> 01:05:38.209
Ms. Jang, I need to talk to you.

944
01:05:39.138 --> 01:05:41.038
Eu Ddeum, wake up. Are you okay?

945
01:05:41.138 --> 01:05:43.149
Ms. Jang, I'll take care of him.

946
01:05:43.249 --> 01:05:44.549
You should go home.

947
01:05:44.549 --> 01:05:46.749
No, I'll deal with him. You should go and help them.

948
01:05:46.749 --> 01:05:49.249
Sir! Help!

949
01:05:49.249 --> 01:05:51.859
I need to talk to Ms. Jang.

950
01:05:52.859 --> 01:05:55.689
- I'll take care of him. - Will you stop?

951
01:05:55.828 --> 01:05:57.959
Ms. Jang, you see...

952
01:05:58.089 --> 01:06:00.499
- I have something to confess. - Eu Ddeum.

953
01:06:00.658 --> 01:06:01.868
Do you recognize me?

954
01:06:03.129 --> 01:06:05.069
- You're my aunt. - What?

955
01:06:07.698 --> 01:06:08.839
You're Ms. Jang.

956
01:06:08.839 --> 01:06:11.808
Okay, stay focused. Come here. Let's go.

957
01:06:12.209 --> 01:06:13.678
- Okay, fine. - My gosh.

958
01:06:13.678 --> 01:06:15.749
- This isn't my car. - It's okay.

959
01:06:16.049 --> 01:06:18.178
Hey, I called a cab for him.

960
01:06:18.178 --> 01:06:20.178
We're going to wait over there. Make sure they go home, okay?

961
01:06:20.718 --> 01:06:22.649
- Okay. - Just get in the car.

962
01:06:22.848 --> 01:06:24.848
- No, I don't want to get in. - You need to get in the car.

963
01:06:24.848 --> 01:06:25.919
This car will take you to the second round.

964
01:06:26.089 --> 01:06:28.058
- But it's not my car. - There you go.

965
01:06:28.058 --> 01:06:30.058
- My car is white. - You're headed to the next round.

966
01:06:30.129 --> 01:06:32.399
- I have something to tell you. - Eu Ddeum.

967
01:06:32.399 --> 01:06:34.229
- Why won't you listen? - Sit down.

968
01:06:34.658 --> 01:06:35.768
My goodness.

969
01:06:39.268 --> 01:06:40.968
Gosh, this is crazy.

970
01:06:42.439 --> 01:06:43.569
Start driving.

971
01:06:56.719 --> 01:07:00.019
I know how you feel.

972
01:07:00.889 --> 01:07:03.688
You should've told me. You must've had such a hard time.

973
01:07:04.828 --> 01:07:06.799
I'm 12 years younger than you.

974
01:07:08.669 --> 01:07:10.629
Why do you keep aging?

975
01:07:11.028 --> 01:07:13.839
What? Has he lost his mind?

976
01:07:15.868 --> 01:07:18.009
You don't need to worry anymore.

977
01:07:18.009 --> 01:07:19.679
I've made up my mind.

978
01:07:20.379 --> 01:07:22.278
Why isn't the cab here yet?

979
01:07:22.549 --> 01:07:24.509
That's not important right now.

980
01:07:31.249 --> 01:07:33.818
Gosh, I'm a complete mess.

981
01:07:35.188 --> 01:07:37.858
Is it because you want to impress me?

982
01:07:38.158 --> 01:07:39.228
My gosh.

983
01:07:50.469 --> 01:07:53.408
I also want to impress you, Ms. Jang.

984
01:07:54.278 --> 01:07:56.148
My goodness.

985
01:07:56.849 --> 01:07:58.078
What's taking the cab so long?

986
01:08:29.478 --> 01:08:31.608
(We thank Jeon Hye Bin for her special appearance.)

987
01:08:51.938 --> 01:08:54.738
(Oh My Baby)

988
01:08:54.969 --> 01:08:56.709
I think I have feelings for Ms. Jang.

989
01:08:56.839 --> 01:08:58.509
I was hoping to ask you two for advice.

990
01:08:58.509 --> 01:09:00.639
We're something like allies, right?

991
01:09:00.639 --> 01:09:02.148
No, we're not.

992
01:09:02.148 --> 01:09:03.679
Actually, go for it.

993
01:09:03.679 --> 01:09:06.948
How dare he kiss me without my permission.

994
01:09:06.948 --> 01:09:09.519
I haven't been kissed for 10 years!

995
01:09:10.988 --> 01:09:12.459
Why does it feel like it's been less than 10?

996
01:09:14.259 --> 01:09:15.459
I think I remember what happened.

997
01:09:16.389 --> 01:09:19.129
Do you actually see me in a romantic way?

998
01:09:19.898 --> 01:09:21.228
All I have for you...

999
01:09:22.669 --> 01:09:23.929
are romantic feelings.

